Arsenal Will Play in Malaysia, China During Pre-Season Soccer Tour of Asia

-- B y   D a n   B a y n e s
-- 
2011-05-24T05:50:40Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-24/arsenal-will-play-in-malaysia-china-during-pre-season-soccer-tour-of-asia.html
Arsenal will travel to  Asia  in July
for a weeklong pre-season tour that takes in matches in Malaysia
and  China .  The Gunners’ first-team squad will face a Malaysia XI on
July 13 at the Bukit Jalil Stadium in  Kuala Lumpur  before taking
on Chinese Super League team Hangzhou GreenTown three days later
in Yiwu City, Arsenal said on its website.  The touring party will then return to  London  to continue
preparations for the 2011-2012 Premier League season, which
starts Aug. 13. Arsenal finished in fourth place this campaign.  Arsenal is also hosting the Emirates Cup on July 30 and 31
at its Emirates Stadium in north London. The four-team
exhibition tournament will this year feature New York Red Bulls,
Paris Saint-Germain and  Argentina ’s Boca Juniors.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dan Baynes at 
 dbaynes@bloomberg.net  